    <string name="help1">Usage</string>
    <string name="help2">The application plots any 3D-surface or multiple surfaces on the same graph.
                    The surface can be time-dependent. Zooming is supported. \n</string>
    <string name="help3">Supported operators</string>
    <string name="help4">\n Add +\n Subtract -\n Multiply *\n Divide /\n Power ^\n
                    Modulus %\n Factorial !\n</string>
    <string name="help5">Available functions</string>
    <string name="help6">Functions can be typed by pressing the \'func\' button on the custom keyboard.
                    If you are not using our custom keyboard, you can type them like in the examples below.
                    Variables φ and θ can be typed like \'phi\' and \'theta\' respectively.\n \n
                    sqrt(): square root\n exp(): exponent\n sin(): sinus\n
                    cos(): cosinus\n tg(): tangent\n ctg(): cotangent\n abs(): absolute value\n
                    log(): logarithm decimal\n ln(): logarithm natural\n asin(): arcsinus\n
                    acos(): arccosinus\n atan(): arctangent\n sh(): hyperbolic sinus\n
                    ch(): hyperbolic cosinus\n </string>
